String:

-immutable(not modifiable) class present in java.lang.* package
-it implements Serializable,comparable and charSequence interface
-string is a sequence of characters

-there are two ways to create string:
1.using String Literal:
-it will we stored inside String constant pool
String s1="welcome";
String s2="welcome";
-Each time u create a string literal,jvm checks string constant pool first.
if the string alraedy exist in the pool a ref to the pooled instance is returned
if string does not exist in the pool a new string instance is created and placed in the pool.
it makes our program memory efficient

2.Using new Keyword:it will store in heap memory
  String str=new String("hello");

methods of String:
1.charAt();
2.length();
3.subString(start index,end Index);//start index is inclussive,end index is exclussive
4.equals();//check contents of string
5.equalsIgnoreCase();
6.isEmpaty();
7.cotains();
8.indexOf();
9.concat();
10.replace();
11.trim();
12.split();

